Hello I am a 20 year old Male

All my life I have had an issue of frequent urination. All my friends and family know I urinate alot and will commonly make comments and it's most been a joke my entire life. "Really man? You already have to go again?" I hear this constantly

I also feel when I drink alot of sugar it comes out more fast. (Soda vs water ect...)

Also it would be good to note I drink alot of coffee (which I hear can help with diabetes or low blood sugar).


I already have gone to the doctors. They did the first one (after I fasted for 8 hours) by drawing blood and doing a urine sample. They told me to come back in again because they got bad results the first one and wanted to do a second. After the second test they tell me as is fine no more tests required. Im also going to mention on the day of the second test I did drink coffee at 4:00 am and had the appointment at 5:00 pm.

One more symptom I have is shaky hands, but this could be from the coffee I drink every day. Also it would be good to mention my family has no history of diabetes on either side.

Should I get the opinion of a second doctor or am I probably just overly worried?


Edit: additional info added for clarity
